post_text:
Mindful Monday:

Good Morning Everyone,
Welcome to the last Mindful Monday of the year! This week's focus is on gratitude and we wanted to send you all into the summer break with an action item that you can carry with you. We hope that you are able to practice mindfulness and self-care throughout the summer and we are looking forward to seeing you all in the Fall!

Please reach out to Ms. Lubisky or Mrs. MacConnell if there is anything that you need while on summer break. You can always email us or fill out the Counselor Contact Request Form if you would like to speak with one of us. https://bit.ly/3cVr9hl

Have a great summer!

post_text:
Dear Families,

Join us this Friday at 7pm when the world of Ancient Greek comedy comes crashing into the 21st century with the MaST Shakespeare Society's digital production of Much Ado About Nothing: Quarantine Edition! Learn more about the show and student actors by perusing our program, and be sure to send love to the cast and crew with our virtual "Kiss the Cast" form during and after the show ends. We are so thankful for all of the support and encouragement we received throughout this entire process, and we hope you will enjoy the show!

Digital Program Playbill: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1FbkdwY1ztmq9rUJ5lMPlKPgbp98SZwPM/view?usp=sharing

Cast Bios: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DmWEGYz948VECJXsNwegIwyAwYlqdbmY/view?usp=sharing

Virtual Kiss the Cast Form:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1BgHSfNLZyL3IHlzpspqaLALv9bdjZZxux_mT7HV2f9w/viewform?edit_requested=true

post_text:
Good afternoon!

On behalf of all of the counselors, we hope that you had a great holiday weekend and were able to enjoy the nice weather with family.

The week's Mindful Monday focuses on reflecting on the school year (what an unpredictable one it was) and paying it forward. Besides improving your mental health by boosting feelings of happiness and positivity, performing acts of kindness can benefit your physical health, too. Even the smallest act of kindness can have a long-lasting impact!

Have a great week!

MaST Schools - Support our Community Night for Restaurants

Dear Families,

We are hosting our first ‚ÄúSupport our community night for restaurants‚Äù.

The following restaurants have reached out and supported us in one way or another over the years.

Some are sponsoring the school for events and some are giving back to the school for every purchase. We want to help our community.

Please help them by placing orders this week for takeout or delivery depending on the restaurant.

Also, please mention that you are a family or supporter of MaST Schools.

I hope everyone is doing well and staying safe.

Thanks,
John F. Swoyer III
Chief Executive Officer

This week's edition of Mindful Monday is about Mindfulness Grounding. It's important to have quick tips in your back pocket for when you are feeling stressed or overwhelmed - something you can use anywhere or anytime. This week's action item will help your mind to stay in the present by keeping you focused on what is happening around you.

Please fill out the Counselor Contact Request Form if you would like a check-in with Ms. Lubisky or Mrs. MacConnell. Your counselors are here to help!

Dear MaST Teachers:

MaST is a great school because we have a wonderful caring staff. Your dedication, patience, and determination is what allows our students to reach for the stars and achieve their dreams.

In this time of uncertainty, you are the voice that comforts, you provide wonderful words of encouragement, and you help our students feel just a little bit better. I am honored to work with each of you!

Happy Teacher Appreciation Week!

Parents and students- please join us in thanking your teachers!

Sincerely,
Phyllis

post_text:
MaST Schools Nurses Week 5/6-12 Thank You Cards

Hello MaST Families,

We are inviting our students to participate in thanking nurses during NATIONAL NURSES WEEK MAY 6-12 by sending them thank you cards to hang up in their hospitals as a visual reminder of our love for them. One hospital in particular reached out to one of our staff and started us thinking.

This is totally optional but what a better way to say THANK YOU!

If your child would like to participate, please read the attached flyer and mail your card directly to the nurse at the hospital by May 5th.

If you would like to thank the nurse(s) at your school, you can take a photo of your card and email it directly to the school nurse.
text:
MaST Schools Nurses Week 5/6-12 Thank You Cards

Hello MaST Families,

We are inviting our students to participate in thanking nurses during NATIONAL NURSES WEEK MAY 6-12 by sending them thank you cards to hang up in their hospitals as a visual reminder of our love for them. One hospital in particular reached out to one of our staff and started us thinking.

This is totally optional but what a better way to say THANK YOU!

If your child would like to participate, please read the attached flyer and mail your card directly to the nurse at the hospital by May 5th.

If you would like to thank the nurse(s) at your school, you can take a photo of your card and email it directly to the school nurse.

post_text:
Please sign this petition and make your voice heard today!
MaST's goal is to receive 1,000 signatures toward a city-wide goal of over 10,000 signatures from charter school advocates and supporters.

Parents and Community Members,
Governor Wolf recently announced his intent to cut $280 million from charter school budgets next year. This would have a disastrous impact on the quality of program we can offer our students. We would have to make tough decisions and cut hundreds of thousands of dollars from our school budget. We need to demand that the Governor and our Philadelphia legislators remember that our students are just as deserving as every other public school student in our state. It is unfair to de-fund charter schools in order to give more money to district schools. We can‚Äôt let this happen.

https://www.change.org/p/gov-wolf-the-philadelphia-delegation-of-pa-state-legislators-stop-governor-wolf-from-cutting-funding-for-mast-s-students

post_text: The 7th graders were honored with a ceremony to end the GREAT Program, presented in conjunction with the Philadelphia Police Department. Officer Stephanie Velazquez has been coming into Mrs. Callahan's class to teach the program over the past few months, and worked with the students on making good choices when faced with difficult situations! post_text: MaST Industrial Arts and Engineering students were present this Manufacturing day for the opening of SureShade's new facility on McNulty Road. After introductions, students listened to speeches on the importance of local manufacturing and the economy. They were given an in-depth tour of the production floor and offices. Thanks to all involved for this amazing opportunity!

post_text: MaST Schools is continuing to look for substitute teachers through its partnership with Kelly Educational Staffing (KES). KES is a partner to over 7,000 schools nationwide who are trusted to provide continuity when teachers are absent. KES does more than any other staffing company to prepare their substitute educators to succeed in every classroom. We are now expanding our sub pool to anyone who is interested in pursuing an emergency certification. If you are interested in becoming an instructional substitute, we invite you to contact KES at 513Z@kellyservices.com or 610-265-0354. For more information about Kelly Educational Staffing, please visit www.kellyeducationalstaffing.com. Kelly Educational Services will also be available at MaST Byberry's Fall Festival on October 7th to answer any questions.
